WEBVTT
X-TIMESTAMP-MAP=MPEGTS:900000,LOCAL:00:00:00.000

00:00:18.101 --> 00:00:20.270 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU]
Yo! Hold up.

00:00:20.353 --> 00:00:22.188 position:50% align:center
Hey, what are you guys doing?

00:00:22.272 --> 00:00:23.648 position:50% align:center
What does it look like?

00:00:23.732 --> 00:00:25.442 position:50% align:center
We're making some gyoza.

00:00:25.525 --> 00:00:27.652 position:50% align:center
Check it out, doesn't
this one look amazing?

00:00:27.736 --> 00:00:30.447 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI] Yeah!
Great job with the folding.

00:00:30.530 --> 00:00:33.241 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU] Crap! We only have six
hours left until the deadline!

00:00:33.324 --> 00:00:35.410 position:50% align:center
Is the manuscript done yet?

00:00:35.493 --> 00:00:39.539 position:50% align:center
Uh, what? "Manuscript"?

00:00:39.622 --> 00:00:41.750 position:50% align:center
Just shut up and fold
the dumplings, fool.

00:00:41.833 --> 00:00:44.294 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI] Look you guys,
this one's perfect!

00:00:44.377 --> 00:00:45.295 position:50% align:center
[RASUNA]
You're killing it.

00:00:45.378 --> 00:00:46.671 position:50% align:center
Well done, Bossman!

00:00:46.755 --> 00:00:48.548 position:50% align:center
[ALL laughing]

00:00:48.631 --> 00:00:51.009 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU] Oh, so this is what
it means to escape reality

00:00:51.092 --> 00:00:52.761 position:50% align:center
right before a tough deadline.

00:00:54.054 --> 00:00:56.556 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR] When a manga artist
wants to escape reality,

00:00:56.639 --> 00:00:59.434 position:50% align:center
they might do so by suddenly
rearranging their room,

00:00:59.517 --> 00:01:01.936 position:50% align:center
or perhaps try cooking
an elaborate dish.

00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:04.647 position:50% align:center
They might even go as far as
cleaning the ventilation fan.

00:01:04.731 --> 00:01:06.232 position:50% align:center
Which, gross.

00:01:06.316 --> 00:01:08.526 position:50% align:center
All of this will bite them
in the ass, of course.

00:01:08.610 --> 00:01:10.195 position:50% align:center
Why don't they just
play video games?

00:01:10.278 --> 00:01:13.406 position:50% align:center
Turns out that makes
them feel too guilty.

00:01:13.490 --> 00:01:17.327 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI grunts]
Okay. Let's get to work.

00:01:17.410 --> 00:01:19.579 position:50% align:center
Hold on. Aren't we
gonna fry these up?

00:01:19.662 --> 00:01:20.914 position:50% align:center
Course not.

00:01:20.997 --> 00:01:23.500 position:50% align:center
'Cause we have a manuscript
to finish, remember?

00:01:23.583 --> 00:01:25.168 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU]
What?

00:01:26.086 --> 00:01:28.838 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU]
We actually did it.

00:01:28.922 --> 00:01:30.507 position:50% align:center
You know, it wouldn't
have been such a crunch

00:01:30.590 --> 00:01:32.801 position:50% align:center
if we hadn't wasted
time making gyoza.

00:01:32.884 --> 00:01:35.261 position:50% align:center
We only did it in time
because we made gyoza!

00:01:35.345 --> 00:01:37.472 position:50% align:center
Jeez, you're such an amateur!

00:01:38.973 --> 00:01:42.560 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU] Huh? That doesn't
make any sense!

00:03:16.363 --> 00:03:18.365 position:50% align:center
[HIME] Currently, my class
is spending some time

00:03:18.448 --> 00:03:20.950 position:50% align:center
at the beach for Summer Camp.

00:03:21.034 --> 00:03:24.454 position:50% align:center
Hey, kids! Make sure you
all have your hats on!

00:03:30.960 --> 00:03:33.129 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI, HIME]
Num Num Time!

00:03:33.213 --> 00:03:36.591 position:50% align:center
I like the curry you make,
it tastes really sweet.

00:03:36.675 --> 00:03:37.967 position:50% align:center
Oh, yeah?

00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:40.220 position:50% align:center
I have some time off,
starting tomorrow.

00:03:40.303 --> 00:03:43.098 position:50% align:center
I thought we could go
somewhere fun together.

00:03:43.181 --> 00:03:46.434 position:50% align:center
But I have to go to summer camp.
We leave tomorrow.

00:03:46.518 --> 00:03:48.269 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI]
What? No one told me!

00:03:48.353 --> 00:03:50.980 position:50% align:center
[HIME] Oh, I gave you a paper
about it over a month ago.

00:03:51.064 --> 00:03:52.357 position:50% align:center
Did you now?

00:03:52.440 --> 00:03:55.485 position:50% align:center
Um... You guys have a lot
of fun things planned?

00:03:55.568 --> 00:04:00.824 position:50% align:center
Yep! Like swimming, and bug
hunts, and building campfires!

00:04:00.907 --> 00:04:05.328 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI] Swimming...
Bug hunts... Giant campfires?

00:04:05.412 --> 00:04:10.166 position:50% align:center
Oh my god. I'm worried.
So worried!

00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:14.629 position:50% align:center
And... Already lonely!

00:04:14.713 --> 00:04:16.339 position:50% align:center
[AOGU] Can't believe we're
taking a company trip

00:04:16.423 --> 00:04:17.882 position:50% align:center
to the ocean. So sick.

00:04:17.966 --> 00:04:20.593 position:50% align:center
[RASUNA] Well, we were overdue
some time off. Let's forget

00:04:20.677 --> 00:04:24.014 position:50% align:center
about manga stuff for a while
and have a little fun!

00:04:24.097 --> 00:04:26.266 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU] So, where exactly
are we staying?

00:04:26.349 --> 00:04:28.852 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI] I borrowed a villa
from a friend of mine.

00:04:28.935 --> 00:04:30.979 position:50% align:center
Whoa, I'm surprised
they let you use it.

00:04:31.062 --> 00:04:33.398 position:50% align:center
We can thank the
Kamakura Fever for that.

00:04:33.481 --> 00:04:35.734 position:50% align:center
Though, technically,
we're going to Chiba.

00:04:35.817 --> 00:04:37.360 position:50% align:center
The whatty what?

00:04:37.444 --> 00:04:39.320 position:50% align:center
Since time immemorial.

00:04:39.404 --> 00:04:44.200 position:50% align:center
This has been a way for manga
artists escape reality.

00:04:44.284 --> 00:04:46.786 position:50% align:center
It all started when a manga
artist became exhausted

00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:48.621 position:50% align:center
by his weekly deadlines.

00:04:48.705 --> 00:04:51.666 position:50% align:center
He couldn't help but fantasize
about a different life

00:04:51.750 --> 00:04:53.835 position:50% align:center
where he could work
by the ocean.

00:04:53.918 --> 00:04:56.129 position:50% align:center
And then one day,
he was able to find a place

00:04:56.212 --> 00:04:59.257 position:50% align:center
to make manga in Kamakura.

00:04:59.341 --> 00:05:04.346 position:50% align:center
But beware. Because this is
where the true terror begins!

00:05:04.429 --> 00:05:06.598 position:50% align:center
It was too far away
for his assistants!

00:05:06.681 --> 00:05:08.683 position:50% align:center
All of the shops closed early!

00:05:08.767 --> 00:05:11.478 position:50% align:center
The salty air made
his pen tips rust!

00:05:11.561 --> 00:05:13.646 position:50% align:center
Yep, in the end they
always get lonely.

00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:17.150 position:50% align:center
And naturally, move back
to Tokyo. A sad tale.

00:05:17.233 --> 00:05:19.194 position:50% align:center
But on the plus side, that's
why it was so easy for us

00:05:19.277 --> 00:05:21.738 position:50% align:center
to borrow a villa for our trip.

00:05:21.821 --> 00:05:23.823 position:50% align:center
[AOGU]
Sure. Makes sense.

00:05:23.907 --> 00:05:25.075 position:50% align:center
[RASUNA]
You guys!

00:05:25.158 --> 00:05:28.661 position:50% align:center
Come on, I said I wanted
to forget about manga.

00:05:31.331 --> 00:05:33.667 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU]
Uh... Is this it?

00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:36.211 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI exhales]
Yep.

00:05:36.294 --> 00:05:39.673 position:50% align:center
Cool, instead of making manga,
we're sweating our balls off.

00:05:39.756 --> 00:05:43.093 position:50% align:center
[AMI] It's eerily similar to
what we do to escape deadlines.

00:05:43.176 --> 00:05:46.179 position:50% align:center
Hold up. Where'd the boss go?

00:05:46.262 --> 00:05:50.725 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI] The real reason I
chose Chiba... is obvious.

00:05:55.438 --> 00:05:57.190 position:50% align:center
[ICHIKO]
Stranger Danger!

00:05:57.273 --> 00:06:00.193 position:50% align:center
Mr. Goto?
What are you doing here?

00:06:00.276 --> 00:06:02.529 position:50% align:center
The thing is...

00:06:02.612 --> 00:06:04.114 position:50% align:center
[ICHIKO]
A company trip?

00:06:04.197 --> 00:06:06.741 position:50% align:center
Yeah, we happened to
be staying nearby.

00:06:06.825 --> 00:06:11.913 position:50% align:center
So you see...
I uh, couldn't help myself.

00:06:11.996 --> 00:06:14.207 position:50% align:center
There was just too much
cuteness to resist.

00:06:14.290 --> 00:06:17.961 position:50% align:center
[gasps] Oh my gosh, please
tell me you're joking!

00:06:18.044 --> 00:06:20.088 position:50% align:center
Never, it's overwhelming.

00:06:21.047 --> 00:06:23.842 position:50% align:center
I'm begging you.
Don't tell Hime about this.

00:06:23.925 --> 00:06:25.218 position:50% align:center
Your secret's safe!

00:06:25.301 --> 00:06:28.013 position:50% align:center
We're going for a rhinoceros
beetle hunt after this,

00:06:28.096 --> 00:06:29.472 position:50% align:center
so that should keep her busy.

00:06:29.556 --> 00:06:30.432 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI gasps]

00:06:30.515 --> 00:06:31.683 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI]
Rhinoceros beetles?

00:06:31.766 --> 00:06:33.435 position:50% align:center
What if Hime's the only
kid who can't catch one

00:06:33.518 --> 00:06:34.811 position:50% align:center
and gets made fun of?

00:06:34.894 --> 00:06:38.148 position:50% align:center
So, uh... Is my cuteness
really that overwhelming?

00:06:38.231 --> 00:06:40.025 position:50% align:center
Oh. He's gone.

00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:41.443 position:50% align:center
Listen up, Kakeru!

00:06:41.526 --> 00:06:42.610 position:50% align:center
Yeah, what's up?

00:06:42.694 --> 00:06:44.154 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI]
Go buy some rhinoceros beetles!

00:06:44.237 --> 00:06:45.030 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:45.113 --> 00:06:47.198 position:50% align:center
The biggest ones you can find.

00:06:49.909 --> 00:06:51.327 position:50% align:center
Okay.

00:06:51.411 --> 00:06:54.164 position:50% align:center
I'll just put 'em someplace
where they're easy to find.

00:06:54.247 --> 00:06:57.167 position:50% align:center
Why in the hell would you buy
a Hercules beetle, huh?!

00:06:57.250 --> 00:06:59.836 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU] Because you said to buy
the biggest one, remember?

00:06:59.919 --> 00:07:01.296 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI] If a little girl
found this in Chiba,

00:07:01.379 --> 00:07:04.674 position:50% align:center
it'd make headlines!
They'll say it was all rigged!

00:07:04.758 --> 00:07:08.011 position:50% align:center
Then her class will vote her off
the island or something!

00:07:08.094 --> 00:07:11.139 position:50% align:center
Forget the bug!
What else could go wrong?

00:07:11.222 --> 00:07:12.807 position:50% align:center
Stranger danger!

00:07:12.891 --> 00:07:15.310 position:50% align:center
Oh, back again?
What's the matter now?

00:07:15.393 --> 00:07:17.854 position:50% align:center
Come on. How was I
supposed to stay away?

00:07:17.937 --> 00:07:20.440 position:50% align:center
You know, from all the cuteness.

00:07:20.523 --> 00:07:22.942 position:50% align:center
[ICHIKO] Can you please
stop saying that?

00:07:23.026 --> 00:07:25.070 position:50% align:center
So, what's next
on the itinerary?

00:07:25.153 --> 00:07:27.280 position:50% align:center
On Sundays I'm usually
just hanging out at home,

00:07:27.364 --> 00:07:28.823 position:50% align:center
so I'm free or whatever.

00:07:28.907 --> 00:07:30.367 position:50% align:center
I meant for the kids.

00:07:30.450 --> 00:07:33.745 position:50% align:center
Duh! They're working
together to make curry.

00:07:33.828 --> 00:07:35.163 position:50% align:center
Hime is super excited

00:07:35.246 --> 00:07:37.082 position:50% align:center
because she's in charge
of seasoning tonight.

00:07:37.165 --> 00:07:38.917 position:50% align:center
She is?

00:07:39.000 --> 00:07:40.835 position:50% align:center
[car braking]

00:07:42.712 --> 00:07:44.339 position:50% align:center
Thanks for coming so quickly.

00:07:44.422 --> 00:07:48.843 position:50% align:center
No problem, my son is a huge fan
of your manga, <i>Balls of Fury.</i>

00:07:48.927 --> 00:07:51.096 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI]
I'm counting on your help.

00:07:53.223 --> 00:07:56.017 position:50% align:center
[RIKO] Hime! Can you
help us wash the rice?

00:07:56.101 --> 00:07:57.143 position:50% align:center
Sure.

00:07:57.227 --> 00:07:59.479 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI]
Go!

00:07:59.562 --> 00:08:00.772 position:50% align:center
[CHEF]
Namaste!

00:08:00.855 --> 00:08:02.315 position:50% align:center
Awesome.

00:08:02.399 --> 00:08:05.860 position:50% align:center
[ICHIKO sighs] I can't believe
he called me cute twice.

00:08:05.944 --> 00:08:09.823 position:50% align:center
Could it be that Mr. Goto
actually thinks about me?

00:08:09.906 --> 00:08:11.658 position:50% align:center
No, you mustn't, Ichiko!

00:08:11.741 --> 00:08:14.160 position:50% align:center
He's the father of one
of your students!

00:08:14.244 --> 00:08:17.163 position:50% align:center
[BOY A]
Hime! That's all wrong!

00:08:17.247 --> 00:08:19.165 position:50% align:center
It's more of a
scratching motion.

00:08:19.249 --> 00:08:23.294 position:50% align:center
Didn't your mom
ever teach you that?

00:08:23.378 --> 00:08:25.046 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:08:26.214 --> 00:08:29.467 position:50% align:center
[HIME]
Okay. I'll try again.

00:08:32.637 --> 00:08:34.055 position:50% align:center
Seriously?

00:08:34.139 --> 00:08:38.935 position:50% align:center
Uh... I just wanted
to check in on Hime.

00:08:39.019 --> 00:08:41.896 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI laughs] I guess
she's always been a bit of

00:08:41.980 --> 00:08:44.941 position:50% align:center
a space cadet, huh?
That's my Hime.

00:08:45.025 --> 00:08:46.693 position:50% align:center
I don't know about that.

00:08:46.776 --> 00:08:47.902 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:08:47.986 --> 00:08:50.071 position:50% align:center
[ICHIKO] Maybe it's not
that she's spaced out.

00:08:50.155 --> 00:08:51.865 position:50% align:center
Maybe it's just more
like she's choosing

00:08:51.948 --> 00:08:54.701 position:50% align:center
not to think about
things too much.

00:08:54.784 --> 00:08:57.579 position:50% align:center
Um, I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have said anything.

00:08:57.662 --> 00:09:00.623 position:50% align:center
Sometimes there are things in
this world you can't change,

00:09:00.707 --> 00:09:02.292 position:50% align:center
no matter how much
you think about them,

00:09:02.375 --> 00:09:04.753 position:50% align:center
you know what I mean?

00:09:04.836 --> 00:09:06.046 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI]
Things you can't change

00:09:06.129 --> 00:09:08.965 position:50% align:center
no matter how much
you think about them?

00:09:09.049 --> 00:09:11.468 position:50% align:center
Maybe, when it comes to her mom,

00:09:11.551 --> 00:09:18.558 position:50% align:center
or my work, she just
chooses to ignore it.

00:09:18.641 --> 00:09:22.687 position:50% align:center
I suppose children have their
own way of escaping reality.

00:09:24.689 --> 00:09:26.483 position:50% align:center
Uh?

00:09:26.566 --> 00:09:29.235 position:50% align:center
[RASUNA] Finally, where
have you been all day?

00:09:29.319 --> 00:09:31.738 position:50% align:center
[AMI] Where's the broom?
I'm going to kill him.

00:09:31.821 --> 00:09:33.239 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU]
I'm so beat.

00:09:33.323 --> 00:09:36.576 position:50% align:center
[AOGU] We were supposed to
be on vacation, but this blows.

00:09:36.659 --> 00:09:39.454 position:50% align:center
Hey. This is still a
vacation, you guys!

00:09:39.537 --> 00:09:42.165 position:50% align:center
Tomorrow's gonna be
jam-packed with fun stuff!

00:09:42.248 --> 00:09:45.251 position:50% align:center
[ALL gasp]
Hooray!

00:09:45.335 --> 00:09:48.171 position:50% align:center
[RASUNA] Yas! I can't wait
to wear my new swimsuit!

00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:50.090 position:50% align:center
[AMI]
And I wanna eat until I die!

00:09:50.173 --> 00:09:51.508 position:50% align:center
[AOGU]
We should totally barbeque!

00:09:51.591 --> 00:09:53.927 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI]
Yeah! Just leave it to me!

00:09:58.264 --> 00:10:01.267 position:50% align:center
[AOGU]
Wow. Life is cruel.

00:10:03.103 --> 00:10:06.356 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI]
Okay. Yeah, please be careful.

00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:08.358 position:50% align:center
They ended Hime's
summer camp early,

00:10:08.441 --> 00:10:10.777 position:50% align:center
and they all went
home this morning.

00:10:10.860 --> 00:10:12.654 position:50% align:center
Well, it is a typhoon.

00:10:12.737 --> 00:10:14.197 position:50% align:center
Why are you wearing
your swimsuit

00:10:14.280 --> 00:10:15.532 position:50% align:center
in the middle of a storm?

00:10:15.615 --> 00:10:17.909 position:50% align:center
Because I wanna get
my money's worth.

00:10:17.992 --> 00:10:20.662 position:50% align:center
It's pretty obvious that
one of us angered fate.

00:10:20.745 --> 00:10:24.624 position:50% align:center
Yeah, forget the ocean,
we can't even step outside.

00:10:24.708 --> 00:10:26.418 position:50% align:center
[AMI gasps]
The power!

00:10:26.501 --> 00:10:27.502 position:50% align:center
[AOGU gasps]

00:10:27.585 --> 00:10:30.296 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU]
And worse! My phone just died!

00:10:31.631 --> 00:10:33.174 position:50% align:center
[KAKERU]
No TV, no games.

00:10:33.258 --> 00:10:34.676 position:50% align:center
[AOGU]
No internet.

00:10:34.759 --> 00:10:36.678 position:50% align:center
Aw man, I'm so bored!

00:10:36.761 --> 00:10:39.264 position:50% align:center
Tell me about it, I read the
lame magazine in the bathroom

00:10:39.347 --> 00:10:40.932 position:50% align:center
like a hundred times.

00:10:41.016 --> 00:10:42.600 position:50% align:center
You sound like spoiled brats.

00:10:42.684 --> 00:10:45.145 position:50% align:center
There are other ways to
pass the time, you know.

00:10:45.228 --> 00:10:46.688 position:50% align:center
Well, since you're
from the ice age,

00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:48.481 position:50% align:center
how'd you pass
the time back then?

00:10:48.565 --> 00:10:51.109 position:50% align:center
[KAKUSHI] Hm?
We'd talk about the wood grain

00:10:51.192 --> 00:10:54.487 position:50% align:center
and how it looked
like famous people.

00:10:54.571 --> 00:10:57.490 position:50% align:center
Or what wrinkles in the curtains
looked the most like a hand.

00:10:57.574 --> 00:10:59.617 position:50% align:center
You guys should totally try it.

00:10:59.701 --> 00:11:01.077 position:50% align:center
[AOGU]
Uh, no.

00:11:01.161 --> 00:11:04.247 position:50% align:center
God, I'm so bored--
I can't take it anymore!

00:11:04.330 --> 00:11:07.083 position:50% align:center
There's gotta be
something to do!

00:11:07.167 --> 00:11:10.211 position:50% align:center
We have paper... and pencils.

00:11:11.212 --> 00:11:14.424 position:50% align:center
[pencil scraping]

00:11:15.133 --> 00:11:16.718 position:50% align:center
What are you doing?

00:11:16.801 --> 00:11:21.014 position:50% align:center
[AMI] Huh? Oh. I thought
I'd draw some manga.

00:11:21.097 --> 00:11:24.059 position:50% align:center
[RASUNA gasps]
Same here!

